CommonFields.Title: Properties of PMMA/Carbon nanotubes nanocomposites prepared by “grafting through” method
Author: Salami-Kalajahi, Mehdi
Haddadi-Asl, Vahid
Behboodi-Sadabad, Farid
Rahimi-Razin, Saeid
Roghani-Mamaqani, Hossein
CommonFields.Location: Department of Polymer Engineering and Color Technology, Amirkabir University of Technology, Tehran, Iran

ChooseParameter.Other: pass through a basic alumina-filled column

Drying-Evaporation.Description: dry overnight before they were used

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: between ambient temperature and 1608C at a frequency of 1 Hz with a sample size of 1 cm * 3 cm.

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: within a range of 500–4,000 cm21 using a resolution of 4 cm21

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The thermograms were obtained between ambient temperature and 6008C at a heating rate of 108C/min.

Raman_Spectroscopy.Equipment: Almega Thermo Nicolet Dispersive Raman Spectrometer
